{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, all participants had to have complete rs-fMRI data and pass the ABCD quality control for their T1 and resting-state fMRI.",
    "This resulted in a total of 4133 participants (2123 female, ages = 9-11).",
    "Additionally, a sample of 2102 (1026 female, ages = 9-11) participants with available follow-up data for all phenotypes from the first follow-up session was used to estimate phenotypic reliability.",
    "The mean interval between the initial imaging session and the follow-up session was 1 year and 11 months.",
    "The ABCD acquisition protocol 91 was harmonised across 21 sites on Siemens Prisma, Phillips, and GE 750 3 T scanners."
  ]
}